Using part1 init, group_recommendations and aggregate_group_mean to make group recommendations lists.
Considering the top 5 recommended movies we try to fing counterfactual explanations to the top
recommended movie.

The designed algorithm combines greedy grow method with diversity cluster representatives. Firts build
classic explanations with greedy grow using movies that most users have rated highly.
Ggreedy grow algorithm gives out an exlpanation list that is in most cases quite long.
We cluster the list with K-Means algorithm to k clusters and select the most influencial
representative from each cluster. The clustering is done with rating patterns the group has given.

Testing is done with 5 random users from the dataset. There is a lot of testig purpose printing.

The program should be run in the folder where the MovieLens data FOLDER is in. The program reads
csv file with path "./ml-100k/u.*". The projectpart1.py file should be in the same folder than
the main file projectpart4.py file. The projectpart1.py file is used to build the initial group
recommendation and to read the data.

working directory
--part4
----projectpart1.py
----projectpart4.py
--ml-100k
----u.*
----...

So in working directory/root run: python .\part4\projectpart4.py